post_text:
Parents/Guardians:
Beginning on Friday, September 4, 2020 through December 22, 2020 all school meals (breakfast and lunch) will be FREE for all students.

For those who currently qualify for free/reduced priced meals, please be sure that your application has been renewed for the 2020 - 2021 school year because the district-wide free meals is a TEMPORARY benefit.

We are offering free meals to our online students too. Go to the tmsd.net website and pre-order for the following week's meals by Friday 1:00 pm.
Pick up is on the first school day of the week between 1 - 1:30 pm; elementary pickup is at the gymnasium entrance and high school pickup is at the band entrance.

Thank you!

post_text:
There will be a ceramic sale featuring student made ceramics during Tussey Mountain Theatre’s presentation of INTO THE WOODS. Other large decorative ceramics will be chanced off, including a TM themed large ceramic vase, water pitcher and a set of TM coffee mugs. Winning names will be drawn on Sunday. Winners do not have to be present to win. $1 a chance or 6 chances for $5. Ceramics will range in price from $1- $15.

This sale includes: coffee mugs, TM Ornaments, deviled egg trays, soap dishes, change trays, flower pots, spoon holders, pie plates, fish baking dishes and many more items.

Sales will benefit Tussey Mountain Theater as well as the TMHS Art Department

Ceramics will be on sale starting at 7 pm Friday and Saturday and Sunday at 2pm.

post_text: Tussey Mountain High School locked down this morning after loud explosions were heard in the vicinity behind the school. In an abundance of caution, we locked down until we determined there was no credible threat. The lockdown has been lifted, and classes have resumed as normal.

post_text: Beginning Friday, 9/13, our afternoon buses will now arrive home 15 minutes earlier. We have eliminated the wait time at the high school. Vo tech students will now travel home separately, arriving at the same time or earlier. Parent pick up times will be ELE 2:50 and HS 3:05 pm.
